---
/**
 * context-engineering 0001 · Figure 2 — the context window as a fixed memory map
 * of competing tenants.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from the source HTML (figure + svg + figcaption incl. footnote
 * <sup>). Lives as an .astro component so the kebab-case SVG attributes render
 * byte-for-byte (MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG). This figure
 * references no arrowhead markers, so it needs no inlined <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 460 322"
        role="img"
        aria-label="The context window as a fixed memory map of competing tenants."
    >
        <text x="230" y="20" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >CONTEXT WINDOW &mdash; one fixed token budget (e.g. ~200k)</text
        >
        <!-- container -->
        <rect
            x="40"
            y="34"
            width="380"
            height="246"
            rx="8"
            fill="#ffffff"
            stroke="#111110"
            stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
        <!-- rows -->
        <rect x="40" y="34" width="380" height="34" fill="#efe7f0"></rect>
        <rect x="40" y="68" width="380" height="30" fill="#f6eef7"></rect>
        <rect x="40" y="98" width="380" height="58" fill="#efe7f0"></rect>
        <rect x="40" y="156" width="380" height="64" fill="#f6eef7"></rect>
        <rect x="40" y="220" width="380" height="26" fill="#efe7f0"></rect>
        <rect x="40" y="246" width="380" height="34" fill="#eef2f7"></rect>
        <!-- dividers -->
        <line x1="40" y1="68" x2="420" y2="68" stroke="#d9d2da"></line>
        <line x1="40" y1="98" x2="420" y2="98" stroke="#d9d2da"></line>
        <line x1="40" y1="156" x2="420" y2="156" stroke="#d9d2da"></line>
        <line x1="40" y1="220" x2="420" y2="220" stroke="#d9d2da"></line>
        <line x1="40" y1="246" x2="420" y2="246" stroke="#b5179e" stroke-dasharray="4 3"></line>
        <!-- labels -->
        <text x="52" y="55" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >System prompt &amp; instructions</text
        >
        <text x="408" y="55" text-anchor="end" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">fixed cost</text>
        <text x="52" y="87" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Tool / function definitions</text
        >
        <text x="408" y="87" text-anchor="end" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">grows with #tools</text>
        <text x="52" y="123" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Conversation history</text
        >
        <text x="52" y="139" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >grows every turn &mdash; the silent budget eater</text
        >
        <text x="52" y="181" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Retrieved context (the part you engineer)</text
        >
        <text x="52" y="197" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
            >docs · code · facts pulled in for THIS question</text
        >
        <text x="52" y="237" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >User's actual question</text
        >
        <text x="52" y="266" font-size="10.5" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
            >&mdash; reserved for the model's answer &mdash;</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Everything competes for one budget. The prompt, tools, and history are <em
            >overhead you pay before the useful part</em
        >. Context engineering fights for the magenta row — and the answer needs room too.<sup
            ><a href="#s1" id="r2">2</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
